place of bioethics in the future of genetics and personalized medicine?

00:30:41.290 --> 00:30:45.510
&gt;&gt; I actually think that bioethics and especially

00:30:45.510 --> 00:30:50.928
a knowledge of genetics is increasingly important, because, you

00:30:50.928 --> 00:30:56.170
know, bio-ethics, as a concept, originated as an

00:30:56.170 --> 00:31:00.300
idea of how to protect participants in research, and

00:31:00.300 --> 00:31:04.830
consumers of healthcare. People who don't have all

00:31:04.830 --> 00:31:08.130
of the training, and the information held by

00:31:08.130 --> 00:31:11.060
the physicians and the researchers, who are, you

00:31:11.060 --> 00:31:13.650
know, bossing them around. Standing there in white

00:31:13.650 --> 00:31:15.700
coats looking scary and saying, give me your

00:31:15.700 --> 00:31:17.280
blood, I'm going to go do great things with

00:31:17.280 --> 00:31:22.980
it. It's important in order to, protect autonomy

00:31:22.980 --> 00:31:25.580
that people have, as we've talked about, informed

00:31:25.580 --> 00:31:28.270
consent. You need to have the information going into

00:31:28.270 --> 00:31:31.400
