00:31:31.400 --> 00:31:34.530
just about giving someone a form when they're coming into

00:31:34.530 --> 00:31:36.930
a study and saying, this is exactly what we're going to

00:31:36.930 --> 00:31:38.620
do, this is what you're going to experience, do you sign

00:31:38.620 --> 00:31:43.870
on the dotted line? Okay. It's about making sure that

00:31:43.870 --> 00:31:48.010
people have the tools to understand their participation in such

00:31:48.010 --> 00:31:51.540
an area, in such a venture in the first place.

00:31:51.540 --> 00:31:53.830
And that's by insuring that people are educated

00:31:53.830 --> 00:31:57.130
about, genetics, about personalized medicine. About, the that

00:31:57.130 --> 00:32:00.120
possibilities their future and their genetic code actually

00:32:00.120 --> 00:32:02.910
hold. What that actually means for them. The

00:32:02.910 --> 00:32:08.160
level of predeterminism, or not. That this information

00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:12.320
actually implies. And, well, I'm perhaps a little

00:32:12.320 --> 00:32:14.180
bit biased in favor of the study of

00:32:14.180 --> 00:32:16.690
bioethics, because I think it is super fun and

00:32:16.690 --> 00:32:22.160
interesting and really important. But, you know science is advancing at

00:32:22.160 --> 00:32:27.170
a pretty breakneck pace, and you know we won't always get out in front

00:32:27.170 --> 00:32:32.270
of it like with GINA, but. Someone needs to be

00:32:32.270 --> 00:32:37.220
paying attention and, you know you never want to say stand

00:32:37.220 --> 00:32:41.700
in the way of any kind of scientific advancement. I don't think that's at all

00:32:41.700 --> 00:32:46.736
what the study of the intersection of ethics and science is about.

00:32:46.736 --> 00:32:47.788
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:32:47.788 --> 00:32:52.720
&gt;&gt; But, ensuring beneficial and responsible use, I think,

00:32:52.720 --> 00:32:56.440
is critical to respecting the people who make research possible.

